article.headline: CS Bakersfield 72, Texas-Pan American 57
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Isaiah Grayson had 15 points and seven assists as Cal State-Bakersfield pulled away in the second half for a 72-57 victory over Texas-Pan American on Saturday night. Mo Hughley added a career-high 14 points for the Roadrunners (8-9), Stephon Carter scored 13, and Donald Johnson had nine points and 13 rebounds. Brandon Provost scored 17 points for Texas-Pan American, which lost despite hitting a season-high 10 3-pointers in 21 attempts. Jared Maree added 12 points for the Broncs (5-13). The game was tied at 46 midway through the second half when Bakersfield went on an 11-0 run to go up 57-46 with 7:27 remaining. Grayson started the surge with a jumper, Zach Lamb and Grayson followed with consecutive 3-pointers, Carter hit a free throw and Hughley capped the run with a layup.
